name: 03 - Data Profiling and Data Exploration
content:
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Data Profiling:

  • Churn distribution across the dataset.
  • Summary statistics for numeric fields (minutes, charges, calls).
  • Frequency analysis of categorical features (intl_plan, voice_mail_plan).

Descriptive Analysis:

  • Churn by State: Identify high churn-prone regions.
  • Churn by Account Length: Compare churn patterns for short vs. long-term customers.
  • Churn vs. Service Calls: Higher churn among customers with frequent customer service calls.
  • Plan Analysis: Customers with intl_plan but low usage tend to churn more.

Visualizations:

  • Histograms for usage distributions (minutes, charges).
  • Boxplots comparing churn vs. non-churn customers across revenue and minutes.
  • Bar plots of churn rate by state and account length groups.
